{"questionId":"13339","questionHtml":"<p>Given that <em>П</em><sub>3</sub>&nbsp;is parallel to the line <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"L\">\n  <mi>L</mi>\n</math></span>, show that <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a + 2b - 5c = 0\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>5</mn>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>normal to <em>П</em><sub>3</sub> is perpendicular to direction of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"L\">\n  <mi>L</mi>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\Rightarrow \\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}} a \\\\   b \\\\   c  \\end{array}} \\right) \\cdot \\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  1 \\\\   2 \\\\   { - 5}  \\end{array}} \\right) = 0\">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mi>a</mi>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mi>b</mi>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mi>c</mi>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>⋅</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>5</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nb